accessibility.text: A girl steps in and says, "My name is Sheng, my English is fairly good out of the class. I can help you translate."
You are bombarded by questions from classmates: "Are Americans all loud?” “Do you regret not learning Chinese?”
What do you think of their questions to you?
Kind of offending.. You don’t want to keep socializing with them
